Nigeria midfielder, Wilfred Ndidi is the second-best tackler in the English Premier League, so far, this season according to the Premier league. Ndidi, who celebrated his 23rd birthday on Monday, has made 72 successful tackles and the record was only better by his Leicester City teammate, Ricardo Pereira, who leads the chart with 74 tackles. Along with his two goals from defensive midfield position, Ndidi has also completed 845 passes, committed 24 fouls and has only been booked twice this season. The midfielder has missed just a league game for the Foxes the season.